title: SpaceX successfully launches its first Falcon Heavy in 40 months
summary: SpaceX now has one more landing—51—than launches this year.

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy launches first U.S. national security mission
summary: A SpaceX Falcon Heavy lifted off Nov. 1 at 9:41 a.m. Eastern from Launch Complex 39A at the Kennedy Space Center, Florida, carrying the U.S. Space Force USSF-44 mission to geostationary Earth orbit.

title: Japanese lunar lander, with NASA rideshare, to launch this month
summary: Japanese lunar lander developer ispace is in the final phases of preparations for the launch of its first lunar lander mission, a flight that will include a NASA lunar cubesat mission as a secondary payload.

title: New guidance from Space Force acquisition boss: ‘The traditional ways must be reformed’
summary: In an Oct. 31 memo, Calvelli laid out nine “space acquisition tenets” intended to drive change in the procurement of space systems

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy lofts USSF-44 on first flight in three years
summary: The world’s most powerful operational rocket, SpaceX’s Falcon Heavy, took to the Florida skies for the first time in over three years November 1 for the USSF-44 mission, a US Space Force contracted flight with a classified payload and at least one rideshare satellite..
